                <head>119. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>At the 458th meeting of the National Security Council on September 7, 1960,
                    discussion included an item on “Civilian Readiness Base,” which was primarily
                    devoted to fallout shelters and stockpiling. (Memorandum of discussion by
                        <persName corresp="#p_JLB1">Johnson</persName>, September 12; <persName
                        corresp="#p_EDD1">Eisenhower</persName> Library, <persName corresp="#p_WAC1"
                        >Whitman</persName> File, <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Records) See
                    the Supplement.</p>
            </div>
